div.p: Assumption: state is stored per-button, and OTHER BUTTON events are always processed before the actual button. Stored state per button is a single bit (up/down), a single state for the state machine across the device is sufficient.
Start the state machine with IS_UP or IS_DOWN based on the button's bit, any OTHER BUTTON event will reset it to that state anyway, so the state can be re-used for the new button.
